text: Australian Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull who met Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe today (2nd Nov.) at the Temple Trees discussed on strengthening economic links, particularly, commerce and investments.During these discussions, a Bilateral Framework Agreement was signed by Secretary to the Ministry of Development Strategies and International Trade Ms. Chandani Wijewardhana and Australian High Commissioner Bryce Hutchesson behalf of the two countries.
title: Australian PM meets SL counterpart
